Class BinaryCategorizerSelector<InputType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.sandia.cognition.util.AbstractCloneableSerializable
      • gov.sandia.cognition.learning.algorithm.ensemble.BinaryCategorizerSelector<InputType>
  • Type Parameters:
    InputType - The type of the input.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BatchLearner<java.util.Collection<? extends InputOutputPair<? extends InputType,java.lang.Boolean>>,BinaryCategorizer<? super InputType>>, SupervisedBatchLearner<InputType,java.lang.Boolean,BinaryCategorizer<? super InputType>>, CloneableSerializable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    @CodeReview(reviewer="Kevin R. Dixon",
            date="2008-07-23",
            changesNeeded=false,
            comments={"Removed implements Serializable, since BatchLearner already does.","Otherwise, looks fine."})
public class BinaryCategorizerSelector<InputType>
extends AbstractCloneableSerializable
implements SupervisedBatchLearner<InputType,java.lang.Boolean,BinaryCategorizer<? super InputType>>
    The BinaryCategorizerSelector class implements a "weak learner" meant for use in boosting algorithms that selects the best BinaryCategorizer from a pre-set list by picking the one with the best weighted error.
    Since:
    2.0
    Author:
    Justin Basilico
